long_desc.thetext:
qx.Class.define("qx.MyClass", {
  construct: function() {
    this.initMyProperty(new qx.data.Array());
  },
  properties : {
    myProperty : { deferredInit : true}
  }
};

Example above should be shown as "init value :  Array" in apiviewer. Indeed it just shows "init value: null". Isn't it?

I agree with you that this would be the desired result. But I'm not sure how easy it is to find out what the real init value will be. Imagine the following case:

qx.Class.define("qx.MyClass", {
  construct: function() {
    this.initMyProperty(some.Static.method());
  },
  properties : {
    myProperty : { deferredInit : true}
  }
};

There is not really a way to get the data from that because the result of the method could depend on states the generator can not know like the OS or browser. I think trying to fix that would only lead part solution and I'm not sure if thats worth the effort.

On the other hand, showing "null" as value is simply wrong and should be changed. Maybe a hint like "in the constructor code" would be ok.
